<item>
  <title>Green bonds</title>
  <link>https://thingsishouldknowasafinanceworker.wordpress.com/2014/12/26/green-bonds/</link>
  <pubDate>Fri, 26 Dec 2014 23:09:23 +0000</pubDate>
  <dc:creator>mrd3v3l0p3r</dc:creator>
  <guid isPermaLink="false">http://thingsishouldknowasafinanceworker.wordpress.com/?p=7</guid>
  <description/>
  <content:encoded><![CDATA[<ul>
	<li>Raise finance for environmentally friendly activities e.g. climate change mitigation or building wind farms</li>
	<li>Usually asset backed or ringfenced, to ensure investors their funds are being used in the stated way</li>
	<li>First bond issued in 2008 by the <em>World Bank</em>, now a predominantly corporate issuer market of $40bn a year</li>
	<li>Useful instrument to offset climate risk (e.g. institutional investors with positions in traditional dirty industrials which may face heavier regulation in the future)</li>
	<li>General lack of standardisation or agreement over what exactly constitutes a green bond, although <em>ICMA</em> are now overseeing a shared set of principles created by 13 banks</li>
</ul>
<h6 class="headline"><a title="Green grow the markets, O" href="http://www.economist.com/news/finance-and-economics/21606326-market-green-bonds-booming-what-makes-bond-green-green-grow">Green grow the markets, O - The Economist</a></h6>
<h6 class="content__headline js-score"><a title="Are green bonds as good as they seem?" href="http://www.theguardian.com/environment/2014/oct/05/are-green-bonds-as-good-as-they-seem">Are green bonds as good as they seem? - The Guardian</a></h6>
<h6><a title="Green Bond Principles - ICMA" href="http://www.icmagroup.org/Regulatory-Policy-and-Market-Practice/green-bonds/">Green Bond Principles - ICMA</a></h6>]]></content:encoded>
