<item>
  <title>Export Credit Agencies</title>
  <link>https://thingsishouldknowasafinanceworker.wordpress.com/2015/05/14/export-credit-agencies/</link>
  <pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2015 18:19:00 +0000</pubDate>
  <dc:creator>mrd3v3l0p3r</dc:creator>
  <guid isPermaLink="false">https://thingsishouldknowasafinanceworker.wordpress.com/?p=19</guid>
  <description/>
  <content:encoded><![CDATA[<ul>
	<li>aka ECAs, Investment Insurance Agencies</li>
	<li>Government funded banks which provide financing to foreign purchasers of domestic products</li>
	<li>Generally fund exports to high risk developing markets where commercial financing is difficult to obtain</li>
	<li>Can provide funds directly, or guarantee borrowing from a private bank</li>
	<li>Big players are the Export-Import Bank of the US and the Japan Bank for International Cooperation.</li>
	<li>UK Export Finance is the UK’s agency</li>
</ul>]]></content:encoded>
